<subSubSection id="8AA429F8405DFF93FF6BFE34994683F3" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C2017A73405DFF93FF6BFE34994683F3" blockId="1.[151,1437,364,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="F0CAA661405DFF93FF6BFE34992D80A7" bold="true" box="[199,308,473,499]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Remarks</emphasis>
. The present juvenile female of 
<taxonomicName id="05BE01F0405DFF93FD0BFE349B3E80A6" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[679,807,473,498]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camposi">
<emphasis id="F0CAA661405DFF93FD0BFE349B3E80A6" box="[679,807,473,498]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">D. camposi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits adult diagnostic features of the pereopods and maxilliped 3 (
<bibRefCitation id="A62F0782405DFF93FE9FFE1199CB8343" author="Ahyong, S. T." box="[307,466,508,535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" pagination="538 - 571" refId="ref2715" refString="Ahyong, S. T. (2018) Revision of Ostracotheres H. Milne Edwards, 1853 (Crustacea: Brachyura: Pinnotheridae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 66, 538 - 571." type="journal article" year="2018">Ahyong 2018</bibRefCitation>
), although the subtle cruciform sculpture of the dorsal surface of the carapace, evident in adults, is not yet developed. 
<bibRefCitation id="A62F0782405DFF93FDA9FDCD9AAD836F" author="Ahyong, S. T." box="[517,692,544,571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" pagination="538 - 571" refId="ref2715" refString="Ahyong, S. T. (2018) Revision of Ostracotheres H. Milne Edwards, 1853 (Crustacea: Brachyura: Pinnotheridae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 66, 538 - 571." type="journal article" year="2018">Ahyong (2018)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="05BE01F0405DFF93FC86FDCC9BB5836E" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[810,940,545,570]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camposi">
<emphasis id="F0CAA661405DFF93FC86FDCC9BB5836E" box="[810,940,545,570]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">D. camposi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from an unidentified species of 
<taxonomicName id="05BE01F0405DFF93FA85FDCC9D85836F" box="[1321,1436,545,571]" class="Bivalvia" family="Spondylidae" genus="Spondylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinoida" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F0CAA661405DFF93FA85FDCC9D85836F" box="[1321,1436,545,571]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Spondylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="05BE01F0405DFF93FF33FDA99928830B" box="[159,305,580,607]" class="Bivalvia" family="Spondylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinoida" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Spondylidae</taxonomicName>
), and the present record confirms 
<taxonomicName id="05BE01F0405DFF93FD14FDA89BD6830B" authority="Sowerby, 1827" authorityName="Sowerby" authorityYear="1827" box="[696,975,580,607]" class="Bivalvia" family="Spondylidae" genus="Spondylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinoida" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis id="F0CAA661405DFF93FD14FDA89B05830A" box="[696,796,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">S. varius</emphasis>
Sowerby, 1827
</taxonomicName>
as a host. 
<taxonomicName id="05BE01F0405DFF93FBE0FDA89D43830A" authorityName="Ahyong" authorityYear="2018" box="[1100,1370,581,607]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Discorsotheres" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camposi">
<emphasis id="F0CAA661405DFF93FBE0FDA89D43830A" box="[1100,1370,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Discorsotheres camposi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is already known from Lifou, but the present specimen represents the first record of the genus and species from 
<collectingCountry id="BAA93AE3405DFF93FACBFD84991083F2" name="New Caledonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
proper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
